{%- comment -%}
  ============================================================
  MISC filter bar — full-width row above the catalog body.

  Desktop layout:
    [320px LEFT cell]                 [REST: pills | sort + per page + count + view toggle]
    FILTER 3  Clear all               ACTIVE  pill pill   Sort by A-Z   Per page 48   N products   [G3][G5][L]

  Mobile layout (<1024px):
    [Filter trigger button]           [Sort by]
    (pills + per page + view toggle are hidden on mobile;
     filter button opens the sidebar drawer)

  Sort and view-toggle are always pinned to the right regardless
  of how many active filter pills exist. Active filter count is a
  small ink badge on the FILTER label in the left cell.

  Inputs:
    - collection        : the collection object (for filters, sort, count)
    - results_url       : the collection URL (for the Clear all link)
    - active_view       : 'grid-3' | 'grid-5' | 'list'
    - per_page          : 24 | 48 | 72 | 96 (current per-page value)
    - enable_list_view  : boolean (hide the List button when false)
  ============================================================
{%- endcomment -%}

{%- liquid
  assign active_count = 0
  for filter in collection.filters
    if filter.type == 'price_range'
      if filter.min_value.value != blank or filter.max_value.value != blank
        assign active_count = active_count | plus: 1
      endif
    else
      assign active_count = active_count | plus: filter.active_values.size
    endif
  endfor
  assign current_sort = collection.sort_by | default: collection.default_sort_by
-%}

{%- comment -%}
  The `active-facets-desktop` class is required so Trade's
  facets.js can replace the inner HTML on every AJAX filter
  change. Without this the pills, count badge, and Clear all
  link don't refresh when the buyer ticks a filter checkbox.
{%- endcomment -%}
<div class="misc-filter-bar active-facets-desktop">

  {%- comment -%} Mobile-only trigger button (hidden on desktop via CSS). {%- endcomment -%}
  <button type="button" class="filter-bar__mobile-trigger" data-mobile-filter-trigger aria-label="Open filters">
    {{- 'icon-filter.svg' | inline_asset_content -}}
    <span>Filter</span>
    {%- if active_count > 0 -%}
      <span class="misc-filter-bar__count">{{ active_count }}</span>
    {%- endif -%}
  </button>

  <div class="misc-filter-bar__left">
    <h2 class="misc-filter-bar__title">
      Filter
      {%- if active_count > 0 -%}
        <span class="misc-filter-bar__count">{{ active_count }}</span>
      {%- endif -%}
    </h2>
    <div class="misc-filter-bar__left-actions">
      {%- if active_count > 0 -%}
        <a href="{{ results_url }}" class="misc-filter-bar__clear">Clear all</a>
      {%- endif -%}
      {%- comment -%}
        MISC: desktop-only collapse toggle. Hides the filter sidebar so
        the table / grid reclaims its width (the list-view Product column
        is squeezed by the 320px sidebar on narrow laptops). State is
        held on <html class="misc-hide-filters"> and persisted in
        localStorage (misc_filters_hidden) by misc-view-toggle.js, with a
        first-paint set in layout/theme.liquid. Label + chevron are driven
        by the html class so they stay correct after facets.js AJAX swaps.
      {%- endcomment -%}
      <button type="button" class="misc-filters-toggle" data-misc-filters-toggle aria-expanded="true" aria-label="Hide filters" title="Hide filters">
        {%- comment -%}
          When filters are shown this is an icon-only chevron (the
          sidebar is right below it, so a text label is redundant and
          would crowd "Clear all" out of the 320px cell). When the
          sidebar is collapsed the cell shrinks to auto width, so we
          reveal the "Show filters" label for discoverability. The
          accessible name is kept correct in both states via aria-label
          (synced in misc-view-toggle.js).
        {%- endcomment -%}
        <span class="misc-filters-toggle__label">Show filters</span>
        <svg class="misc-filters-toggle__chevron" width="10" height="10" viewBox="0 0 10 10" fill="none" aria-hidden="true">
          <path d="M6.5 1.5 3 5l3.5 3.5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
        </svg>
      </button>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="misc-filter-bar__right">

    {%- comment -%} ACTIVE PILLS — left side of right cell. Hidden on mobile. {%- endcomment -%}
    <div class="misc-filter-bar__pills">
      {%- if active_count > 0 -%}
        <span class="misc-filter-bar__label">Active</span>
        {%- for filter in collection.filters -%}
          {%- if filter.type == 'price_range' -%}
            {%- if filter.min_value.value != blank or filter.max_value.value != blank -%}
              <a href="{{ filter.url_to_remove }}" class="misc-applied-pill">
                {{ filter.min_value.value | default: 0 | money }}&ndash;{{ filter.max_value.value | default: filter.range_max | money }}
                <span class="misc-applied-pill__close" aria-hidden="true">&times;</span>
              </a>
            {%- endif -%}
          {%- else -%}
            {%- for value in filter.active_values -%}
              <a href="{{ value.url_to_remove }}" class="misc-applied-pill">
                {{ value.label }}
                <span class="misc-applied-pill__close" aria-hidden="true">&times;</span>
              </a>
            {%- endfor -%}
          {%- endif -%}
        {%- endfor -%}
      {%- endif -%}
    </div>

    {%- comment -%} TOOLS — pinned to the right edge regardless of pills count. {%- endcomment -%}
    <div class="misc-filter-bar__tools">

      {%- comment -%} Sort dropdown. The change handler is wired in
                     misc-view-toggle.js via event delegation on the
                     #MiscSortBy id so it survives AJAX filter swaps. {%- endcomment -%}
      <div class="sort-control">
        <label class="sort-control__label" for="MiscSortBy">Sort by:</label>
        <select id="MiscSortBy" class="sort-control__select">
          {%- for option in collection.sort_options -%}
            <option value="{{ option.value | escape }}"{% if option.value == current_sort %} selected{% endif %}>
              {{- option.name | escape -}}
            </option>
          {%- endfor -%}
        </select>
      </div>

      {%- comment -%}
        Per-page dropdown. Driven by Shopify's native template
        variant mechanism: ?view=per-N loads collection.per-N.json
        which overrides the section's products_per_page setting.
        The current value comes from section.settings.products_per_page
        (which the active template overrides).
      {%- endcomment -%}
      <div class="sort-control sort-control--per-page">
        <label class="sort-control__label" for="MiscPerPage">Per page:</label>
        <select id="MiscPerPage" class="sort-control__select">
          {%- assign per_page_options = '24,48,72,96' | split: ',' -%}
          {%- assign current_per_page_num = section.settings.products_per_page | plus: 0 -%}
          {%- for option in per_page_options -%}
            {%- assign option_num = option | plus: 0 -%}
            <option value="{{ option }}"{% if option_num == current_per_page_num %} selected{% endif %}>{{ option }}</option>
          {%- endfor -%}
        </select>
      </div>

      <span class="sort-control__count">{{ collection.products_count }} products</span>

      {%- comment -%} Layout toggle: Grid 3 / Grid 5 / List. JS in misc-view-toggle.js
                     handles the swap + URL update via ?layout=. {%- endcomment -%}
      <div class="view-toggle" role="group" aria-label="View density">
        <button type="button" class="view-toggle__btn{% if active_view == 'grid-3' %} is-active{% endif %}" data-layout="grid-3">Grid 3</button>
        <button type="button" class="view-toggle__btn{% if active_view == 'grid-5' %} is-active{% endif %}" data-layout="grid-5">Grid 5</button>
        {%- if enable_list_view -%}
          <button type="button" class="view-toggle__btn{% if active_view == 'list' %} is-active{% endif %}" data-layout="list">List</button>
        {%- endif -%}
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</div>
